# Documentation Rules

Docs are the source of truth for implementation. When behavior changes, update docs in the same change.

## What to update when

| Change | Update |
|---|---|
| Public API / UX | `README.md` quickstart + examples; Google docstrings |
| Architecture / milestones | `PLAN.md` (keep stable unless design changes) |
| Checklist progress | `TASKS.md` checkboxes |
| User-facing release notes | `CHANGELOG.md` |
| Repo layout | `STRUCTURE.md` |

## Rules

- Keep docstrings synchronized with signatures and behavior.
- Explain non-obvious algorithms (adapter resolution, wrap detection order, pipeline flatten) in code comments or `PLAN.md` — not duplicated in every file.
- Do not invent features in docs that are not in `PRD.md` / `PLAN.md` without asking.
- Simulated demos/playgrounds must be labeled illustrative (`PRD.md` §9).
- Prefer cross-links between docs over copy-pasting the same content.

## Doc purpose split (do not collapse)

- `PRD.md` — what/why
- `PLAN.md` — how
- `STRUCTURE.md` — where
- `TASKS.md` — execution checklist
- `README.md` — entry point for humans
